<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>gschur  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="gschur"> generalized Schur form (matrix pencils).  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[As,Es]=gschur(A,E)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[As,Es,Q,Z]=gschur(A,E)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[As,Es,Z,dim] = gschur(A,E,flag)   </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[As,Es,Z,dim]= gschur(A,E,extern)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>A, E  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : two real square matrices
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>flag  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : character string (<VERB>&apos;c&apos;</VERB> or <VERB>&apos;d&apos;</VERB>)
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>extern  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : Scilab ``external&apos;&apos; function (usual case). Could be also a list or a character string
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>As,Es  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : two real square matrices
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>Q, Z  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : two non-singular real matrices
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>dim  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : integer (dimension of subspace)
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    Schur form of matrix pencils (QZ algorithm):
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
[As,Es] = gschur(A,E)
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    produces a quasi triangular <VERB>As</VERB> matrix
    and a triangular <VERB>Es</VERB> matrix which are the generalized
    Schur form of the pair <VERB>A, E</VERB>.
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
[As,Es,Q,Z] = gschur(A,E)
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    returns in addition two unitary matrices
    <VERB>Q</VERB> and <VERB>Z</VERB> such that <VERB>As=Q*A*Z</VERB> and <VERB>Es=Q*E*Z</VERB>. 
  </P>
  <P>
    Ordered stable form:
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
[As,Es,Z,dim] = gschur(A,E,'c')
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    returns the real generalized
    Schur form of the pencil <VERB>s*E-A</VERB>. In addition, the dim first columns 
    of <VERB>Z</VERB> span a basis of the right eigenspace  associated with 
    eigenvalues with negative real parts (stable &quot;continuous
    time&quot; generalized eigenspace).
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
[As,Es,Z,dim] = gschur(A,E,'d')
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    returns the real generalized
    Schur form of the pencil <VERB>s*E-A</VERB>. In addition, the dim first columns 
    of <VERB>Z</VERB> make a basis of the right eigenspace  associated with 
    eigenvalues with magnitude lower than 1 (stable &quot;discrete
    time&quot; generalized eigenspace).
  </P>
  <P>
    General subspace:
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
[As,Es,Z,dim] = gschur(A,E,extern)
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    returns the real generalized Schur form of the pencil <VERB>s*E-A</VERB>. 
    In addition, the dim first columns 
    of <VERB>Z</VERB> make a basis of the right eigenspace  associated with 
    eigenvalues of the pencil which are selected according to a
    rule which is given by the scilab function extern.
    (See <VERB>schur</VERB> for definition of this function).
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
s=%s;
F=[-1,s,0,0;0,-1,0,0;0,0,2+s,0;0,0,0,-2+s];
roots(det(F))
[E,A]=pen2ea(F);
[As,Es,Z,dim] = gschur(A,E,'c')
// Other example
a=rand(4,4);b=rand(4,4);[as,bs,qs,zs]=gschur(a,b);
norm(qs*a*zs-as)
norm(qs*b*zs-bs )
clear a;
a(8,8)=2;a(1,8)=1;a(2,[2,3,4,5])=[0.3,0.2,4,6];a(3,[2,3])=[-0.2,.3];
a(3,7)=.5;
a(4,4)=.5;a(4,6)=2;a(5,5)=1;a(6,6)=4;a(6,7)=2.5;a(7,6)=-10;a(7,7)=4;
b=eye(8,8);b(5,5)=0;
[al,be]=gspec(a,b);
[bs,as,q,n]=gschur(b,a,'disc');n-4
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
